metadata.name: Miktlāntēkwtli
metadata.description: This piece of art is inspired by three old aztec gods: Mictlantecutli (representing God of death), Xolotl (representing God of the underworld),  and Cipactli (representing God of the earth and agriculture). This image is a photographic registration with just a color adjustment, the original piece is done with these specific techniques: matte spray, airbrush and acrylic.
